Hindalco, HPCL, Maruti, Reliance, Sun TV: India Equity Preview

-- B y   A n o o p   A g r a w a l   a n d   R a j h k u m a r   K   S h a a w
-- 
2011-10-10T03:18:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-10/hindalco-reliance-tata-consultancy-india-stocks-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in  India  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the last close.  The Bombay Stock Exchange Sensitive Index, or Sensex, rose
2.8 percent to 16,232.54. The S&P CNX Nifty Index on the
National Stock Exchange jumped 2.9 percent to 4888.05. The BSE
200 Index advanced 2.4 percent to 1,996.81. SGX S&P CNX Nifty
Index futures for October delivery climbed 0.3 percent to 4,907
as of 11:08 a.m. in  Singapore .  Hindalco Industries Ltd. (HNDL)  : India’s biggest
aluminum producer was raised to “overweight” from “neutral”
at JPMorgan by analyst Pinakin Parekh on Oct. 7, with a price
target of 170 rupees a share. The stock gained 4.8 percent to
125.9 rupees.  Hindustan Petroleum Corp. (HPCL IN): The state-run refiner
is likely to acquire a oil and gas block in Africa through its
subsidiary, Prize Petroleum, Business Standard reported without
saying where it got the information. The shares declined 0.9
percent to 367.85 rupees.  Maruti Suzuki India Ltd. (MSIL)  : The maker of almost
half the cars sold in India halted production again at its
Manesar plant, outside  New Delhi , after some workers went on
strike on Oct. 7, said a spokesman who declined to be
identified, citing company policy. The shares rose 2.6 percent
to 1,113.2 rupees.  Mercator Lines Ltd. (MRLN)  : India’s second-largest
shipping company is in talks to purchase “a couple of more”
dredgers to add to its fleet of five, Atul Agarwal, managing
director and chief financial officer, said in an e-mail. He
didn’t say how much money the company would spend on the
purchases. The shares added 3.4 percent to 23.05 rupees.  Prism Informatics Ltd. (PILT)  : The company won a
contract from a elevator manufacturer in Gujarat state. The
shares rose 1 percent to 63.45 rupees.  Reliance Industries Ltd. (RIL)  : India’s most valuable
company will report earnings for the quarter ended Sept. 30 on
Oct. 15, it said in a statement.  Separately, the company is set to sign a deal with Walt
Disney Co.’s local subsidiary  UTV Software Communications Ltd. (UTV) 
 in the coming weeks, the Financial Times reported
Sunday on its website, citing unnamed sources. Reliance rose 4.7
percent to 802.9 rupees. UTV fell 0.1 percent to 943.35 rupees.  Sun TV Network Ltd. (SUNTV)  : India’s federal
investigators searched the homes and offices of former
telecommunications minister Dayanidhi Maran and Sun TV Chairman
Kalanithi Maran, NDTV television channel reported today. Dharini
Mishra, a spokeswoman for the Central Bureau of Investigation,
said she is unable to confirm the search. The shares jumped 14
percent to 262.9 rupees.  Suzlon Energy Ltd. (SUEL)  : The founders of India’s
biggest wind-turbine maker have pledged 37.57 percent of the
company’s equity, according to a statement to the stock-
exchange. The shares rose 3.2 percent to 35.95 rupees.  Tata Consultancy Services Ltd. (TCS)  : India’s largest
software exporter plans to triple the number of its employees in
 China  within three years, from 2,000 currently, the China Daily
reported on Oct. 8, citing Girija Pande, chairman of the
company’s Asia-Pacific operations. Tata plans to hire 70,000
people globally this year, the paper said. The shares rose 0.5
percent to 1,048.55 rupees.  Unity Infraprojects Ltd. (UIP)  : The developer said on
Oct. 7 it got orders worth 4.03 billion rupees ($82 million).
The shares rose 1.5 percent to 41.65 rupees.  Vertex Securities Ltd. (VRTS)  : The company will consider
at a meeting tomorrow a proposal to demerge its merchant-banking
unit into a new company. The shares rose 1.9 percent to 234.7
rupees.  To contact the reporters on this story:
